0. Summary

By this License, OpenMobile World Wide, Inc. ("We" or "Our") grants to
an original equipment manufacturer, silicon chip vendor, or mobile
network operator ("You" or "Your") a limited right to distribute Our
Generic Service Loader software ("GSL") preloaded on Your Firefox OS
Devices (defined below) for the limited purpose of making those devices
ACL-Ready (defined below). We do so only if You abide by the terms
below.

1. Definitions

1.1. "ACL-Ready" means a Firefox OS Device (defined below) that supports
download and installation of Our Application Compatibility Layer
software ("ACL") by an end user of that device.

1.2. "Covered Software" means the Source Code Form of Our Generic
Service Loader software ("GSL") with which this License is provided by
Us to You and the Executable Form of GSL.

1.3. "Source Code Form" means the human-readable form of GSL that we are
providing to you with this License.

1.4. "Executable Form" means object code or other computer-readable
forms of GSL generated by a compiler (and/or other related automated
software tools) from the Source Code Form.

1.5. "Firefox OS Device" means a mobile phone or other processor-based
device on which the "Firefox OS" operating system is pre-loaded as the
native operating system.

1.6. "License" means this document.
1.7. "You" (or "Your") means an original equipment manufacturer, silicon
chip vendor, or mobile network operator. "You" includes any entity that
is controlled by You. For purposes of this definition, "control" means
the power, direct or indirect, to cause the direction or management of
such entity, whether by contract or otherwise.

1.8. "Your Firefox OS Devices" means Firefox OS Devices made and/or
distributed by you to end users, directly or otherwise.

1.9. "We" (or "Our" or "Us") means OpenMobile World Wide, Inc., having
a principal place of business in Framingham, Massachusetts, USA.

